==Philanthropy==
In 2011, McCreery participated in Operation Christmas Child, a program dedicated to donating toys to impoverished children around the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/scotty-mccreery-american-idol-winner-lends-helping-hand-with-operation-christmas-child-62719/|first=Justin|last=Sarachik|title=Scotty McCreery American Idol Winner Lends Helping Hand With Operation Christmas Child|work=Christian Post Reporter|date=November 22, 2011|access-date=April 1, 2015}}</ref> Every year since then, he has participated in the [[City of Hope (charity)|City of Hope]] Celebrity Softball Game, which raises funds for cancer research.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theboot.com/city-of-hope-softball-game-nashville-2011/|first=Erin |last=Duvall |title=Country Stars Step Up to the Plate for City of Hope|work=[[Townsquare Media|The Boot]]|date=June 13, 2011|access-date=April 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/city-of-hope-softball-game-scotty-mccreery-carrie-underwood/|first=Alanna |last=Conaway |title=Carrie Underwood, Scotty McCreery + More Step Up to the Plate for City of Hope Softball Challenge|work=Taste of Country|date=June 10, 2012|access-date=April 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://theboot.com/country-stars-2013-city-of-hope-softball-game/|title=Country Stars Pitch in to Fight Cancer at 2013 City of Hope Softball Game|work=The Boot|date=June 8, 2013|access-date=April 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/florida-georgia-line-scotty-mccreery-city-of-hope-softball-game-photos/|first=Billy |last=Dukes |title=Florida Georgia Line, Scotty McCreery + More Suit Up for City of Hope Softball Game [Photos]|work=Taste of Country|date=June 7, 2014|access-date=April 6, 2015}}</ref> He performed a benefit concert in November 2012, through which he raised $5,000 for [[World Vision]] to help with the [[Hurricane Sandy]] relief efforts,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/112920/scotty-mccreery-benefit-concert-raises-5-000-for-h|title=Scotty McCreery Benefit Concert Raises $5,000 For Hurricane Relief|work=Allaccess.com|date=November 27, 2012|access-date=April 7, 2015}}</ref> and the following year, World Vision acted as the charitable sponsor for McCreery's Weekend Roadtrip Tour (2013).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wvartists.org/article/scotty-mccreery-partners-with-world-vision-on-his-weekend-roadtrip-tour/|first=Lori|last=Christian|title=SCOTTY MCCREERY PARTNERS WITH WORLD VISION ON HIS WEEKEND ROADTRIP TOUR|work=[[World Vision]]|date=January 31, 2013|access-date=April 7, 2015}}</ref> Over the course of a 2013 [[Major League Baseball]] [[ballpark]] tour, McCreery donated $50,000 to various youth baseball programs across the United States, including Major League Baseball's [[Reviving Baseball in Inner Cities]] (RBI) program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.umgnashville.com/news/scotty-mccreery-launches-six-city-tour-of-mlb-parks/|title=SCOTTY MCCREERY LAUNCHES SIX-CITY TOUR OF MLB PARKS|work=[[UMG Nashville]]|date=September 19, 2013|access-date=April 8, 2015}}</ref> McCreery became a National Goodwill Ambassador for the 12.14 Foundation in February 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.1214foundation.org/scotty-mccreery/ |title=Scotty McCreery - 1214 Foundation |access-date=April 1, 2015 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402115349/http://www.1214foundation.org/scotty-mccreery/ |archive-date=April 2, 2015  }}</ref> He has an active role in promoting the Foundation's arts program, supporting their fundraising efforts, and creating awareness for their vision and objectives to help the people of [[Newtown, Connecticut]]. On December 4, 2014, McCreery performed a benefit concert which raised $60,000 to the foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tasteofcountry.com/scotty-mccreery-fundraiser-12-14-foundation/|title=Scotty McCreery Raises $60,000 for 12.14 Foundation|website=Taste of Country|date=December 6, 2014 |access-date=May 8, 2018}}</ref> In December 2017, McCreery and other country artists recorded a charity single, a cover of [[Alabama (American band)|Alabama's]] "[[Angels Among Us]]," to benefit [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital]].<ref name="Angels Among Us">{{cite web|title= Scotty McCreery, Carly Pearce and More Record 'Angels Among Us' For St. Jude Children's Research Hospital|url=http://www.soundslikenashville.com/news/carly-pearce-scotty-mccreery-angels-among-us-country-cares/|work=Sounds Like Nashville|date=December 7, 2017|access-date=September 4, 2019}}</ref> McCreery appeared on "[[Celebrity Family Feud]]" on August 5, 2018, and won $25,000 for St. Jude Children's Research Hospital.<ref name="$25,000"/>

==Honors and awards==
In 2017 McCreery received the [[Order of the Long Leaf Pine]], the highest civilian award given by the State of North Carolina. He received the award on stage at a performance at the [[Grand Ole Opry]] in Nashville, Tennessee. He was nominated for the award by outgoing governor [[Pat McCrory]] and conferred the award by his replacement [[Roy Cooper]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ogburn|first1=Thad|title=Scotty McCreery's latest honor is a matter of state pride|url=http://www.newsobserver.com/entertainment/article141461049.html|website=Newsandobserver.com|access-date=April 3, 2018}}</ref>

In 2024, McCreery was inducted as a [[List of Grand Ole Opry members|member]] of the [[Grand Ole Opry]], following an invitation by [[Garth Brooks]] in December 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tennessean.com/story/entertainment/music/2023/12/04/scotty-mccreery-invited-by-garth-brooks-to-become-newest-grand-ole-opry-member/71798225007/|title=Scotty McCreery invited by Garth Brooks to become newest Grand Ole Opry member|website=The Tennessean}}</ref>

